main event: A silver-colored object was observed changing elevation rapidly, resulting in a smoke screen and an explosion in the upper atmosphere.
interesting points: A shockwave was felt that shook buildings in the area., The object changed elevation at a rate of 25-35 m/minute., A ball of flame was observed coming from the object, changing color., There was a smell of burning or a vapor trail for the duration of the sighting., The observation lasted for about 5-6 minutes according to the Ground Observer Corps.
